Area-based Assessment: to better understand protection and social cohesion issues and stakeholders in the city, including an investigation of the formal and informal mechanisms residents use to seek protection and to make protection-related decisions

Area-based Assessment: to provide humanitarian-development-peace ‘nexus’ actors with information related to service delivery and social cohesion in the city, and identify efficient and conflict-sensitive entry points for supporting medium- to long-term solutions to service delivery challenges.

Labour market assessments - The assessment aims to understand the structure of the labour market, opportunities that are present, and barriers to accessing the labour market for different segments of the population.

Specifically, the assessment aims to map out the characteristics of the labour market, how Libyans and non-Libyans interact with the labour market and the opportunities and challenges for each population group. The labour market assessments will include a stakeholder mapping identifying local structures focused on economic development in the target areas.
